gurmukhi: ਨ ਪੁੱਤ੍ਰੰ ਨ ਮਿੱਤ੍ਰੰ ਨ ਸੱਤ੍ਰੰ ਨ ਭਾਮੰ ॥
transliteration: Na Pouttran Na Mittran, Na Sattran Na Bhaamannd||
translation: He is without son, without friend, without enemy and without wife.
He is accountless, guiseless, and Unborn entity.

gurmukhi: ਸਦਾ ਸਿੱਧ ਦਾ ਬੁੱਧਿ ਦਾ ਬ੍ਰਿੱਧ ਰੂਪੰ ॥੨॥੯੨॥
transliteration: Sadaa Siddh Daa Buddh(i) Daa Briddh Roopan||2||92||
translation: He is ever the Giver of Power and Intellect, He is most Beautiful. 2.92.

gurmukhi: ਨਹੀਂ ਜਾਨ ਜਾੲੀ ਕਛੂ ਰੂਪ ਰੇਖੰ ॥
transliteration: Nahoon Jaan Jaai Kachhodh Roop Rekhan||
translation: Nothing can be known about His Form and Mark.

gurmukhi: ਕਹਾ ਬਾਸੁ ਤਾ ਕੋ ਫਿਰੈ ਕੳੁਨ ਭੇਖੰ ॥
transliteration: Kahaa Baas(u) Taa Ko Phirai Kaoun Bhekhan||
translation: Where doth He live? In what Garb He moves?

gurmukhi: ਕਹਾ ਨਾਮ ਤਾ ਕੈ ਕਹਾ ਕੈ ਕਹਾਵੈ ॥
transliteration: Kahaa Naam Taa Kai Kahaa Kai Kahaavai||
translation: What is His Name? Of what Place He is told?

gurmukhi: ਕਹਾ ਕੈ ਬਖਾਨੋ ਕਹੇ ਮੋ ਨ ਅਾਵੈ ॥੩॥੯੩॥
transliteration: Kahaa Kai Bakhaano Kahe Mo Na Aavai||3||93||
translation: How should He be described? Nothing can be said. 3.93.

gurmukhi: ਨ ਰੋਗੰ ਨ ਸੋਗੰ ਨ ਮੋਹੰ ਨ ਮਾਤੰ ॥
transliteration: Na Rogadg Na Sogadg, Na Mohan Na Maatan||
translation: He is without ailment, without sorrow, without attachment and without mother.

gurmukhi: ਨ ਕਰਮੰ ਨ ਭਰਮੰ ਨ ਜਨਮੰ ਨ ਜਾਤੰ ॥
transliteration: Na Karamannd Na Bharamannd, Na Janamannd Na Jaatan||
translation: He is without work, without illusion, without birth and without caste.
He is without malice, without guise, and Unborn Entity.

gurmukhi: ਨਮੋ ੲੇਕ ਰੂਪੇ ਨਮੋ ੲੇਕ ਰੂਪੇ ॥੪॥੯੪॥
transliteration: Namo Ek Roope, Namo Ek Roope||4||94||
translation: Salutation to Him of One Form, Salutation to Him of One Form. 4.94.
Yonder and Yonder is He, the Supreme Lord, He is the Illuminator of Intellect.
He is Invincible, Indestructible, the Primal, Non-dual and Eternal.

gurmukhi: ਨ ਜਾਤੰ ਨ ਪਾਤੰ ਨ ਰੂਪੰ ਨ ਰੰਗੇ ॥
transliteration: Na Jaatan Na Paatan Na Roopan Na Rane||
translation: He is without caste, without line, without form and without colour.
